## Running the Project

Open two terminals. One for back-end:

```sh
# Terminal 1 -> Back-end
cd ./back-end             # Enter the back-end directory
npm install               # Install necessary dependencies
node ./express-server.js  # Run the server ( http://localhost:8080/ )
```

And one for front-end:

```sh
# Terminal 2 -> Front-end
cd ./front-end            # Enter the front-end directory
npm install               # Install necessary dependencies
npm start                 # Run the React application ( http://localhost:3000/ )
```

The end-user should visit the React application in their web browser via:

[http://localhost:3000/](http://localhost:3000/)

If you want to check to see if your back-end is working correctly, here is a sample URL that should be functional:

[http://localhost:8080/api/todos/](http://localhost:8080/api/todos/)

## The Project Stack

This project uses a ER (Express/React) stack. The breakdown is as follows:
* Express: The API back-end; delivers JSON responses.
* React: The front-end web page; the user interface, capable of ajax requests.

### ROUTES

* API end-points on back-end (we want to Ajax to these...)
    * `GET  /api/todos`              -> provide list of all to-dos
    * `POST /api/todos`              -> submit a new to-do
      * RESTFUL: `POST`
    * `POST /api/todos/:id/delete`   -> remove to-do
      * RESTFUL: `DELETE`
    * `POST /api/todos/:id`          -> update to-do
      * RESTFUL: `PUT`
    * `POST /api/todos/:id/complete` -> complete to-do
      * RESTFUL: `PATCH`
